html(lang="en", ng-app="DemoApp")
	head
		link(href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/twitter-bootstrap/2.3.1/css/bootstrap-combined.min.css",rel="stylesheet")
		link(rel="stylesheet", href="angular.ratings.css")

	body.container(ng-controller="DemoCtrl")
		|<a href="https://github.com/thomporter/angular-ratings"><img style="position: fixed; top: 0; right: 0; border: 0;" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/github/ribbons/forkme_right_darkblue_121621.png" alt="Fork me on GitHub"></a>
		h1 Angular Ratings 
			small Cool Angular Rating Icons Included!
		p A diretive to help out with rating systems on your Angular powered website.
		p In the first 2 demos, we're binding directly to a property on the scope of our controller, probably not 
			| ever going to happen in the real world, but it makes for a super simple exmpale.

		h2 Demo 1 
			small Interactive
		p A ratings widget that is editable by the user.
		.row-fluid
			.span3
				angular-ratings(notify-url="notify.json", notify-id="id", ng-model="user_rating")
			.span9
				pre
					|<angular-ratings ng-model="user_rating" notify-url="notify.json" notify-id="id">
		hr
		h2 Demo 2 
			small Display
		p Based on a static value not editable by the user, good for showing the average rating of something.
			| This is accomplished by simply leaving out the notify-url.
		.row-fluid
			.span3
				angular-ratings(ng-model="avg_rating")
			.span9
				pre
					|<angular-ratings ng-model="user_rating">
		hr
		
		h2 Demo 3 
			small Usage in a list
		p In this demo we'll be a little more realistic.  Here our controller has a list of items, each with an id, 
			| name and rating.  It also has an object called "user_ratings" that represents the active user's ratings.
			| It uses the item id's as keys, with the user's rating as values.  This allows us to access the ratings
			| for each item like so: user_ratings[item.id]
		.row-fluid
			.span3
				.item(ng-repeat="item in items")
					h5 {{item.name}}
					.row-fluid
						.span6
							strong Your Rating
							angular-ratings(notify-url="notify.json", notify-id="id", ng-model="user_ratings[item.id]")
						.span6
							strong Average Rating
							angular-ratings(ng-model="item.avg_rating")
			.span9
				pre
					|<div ng-repeat="item in items" class="item">
					|   <h5>{{item.name}}</h5>
					|   <div class="row-fluid">
					|      <div class="span6">
					|         <strong>Your Rating</strong>
					|         <angular-ratings notify-url="notify.json" notify-id="id" ng-model="user_ratings[item.id]"></angular-ratings>
					|      </div>
					|      <div class="span6">
					|         <strong>Average Rating</strong>
					|         <angular-ratings ng-model="item.avg_rating"></angular-ratings>
					|      </div>
					|   </div>
					|</div>
